This is an AE which is a painful type of osteochondrosis where the cartilage or bone in a joint is inflamed.

This is an AE which is a family of orthopedic diseases of the joint that occur in children, adolescents and rapidly growing animals, particularly pigs, horses, dogs, and broiler chickens.

This is an AE which is a group of genetic disorders that all result in bone that breaks easily.[9][1]: 85  The range of symptoms—on the skeleton as well as on the body's other organs—may be mild to severe.
This is an AE which is a new piece of bone usually growing on another piece of bone, typically the skull.

This is an AE which is a disease characterized by the softening of the bones caused by impaired bone metabolism primarily due to inadequate levels of available phosphate, calcium, and vitamin D, or because of resorption of calcium.

This is an AE which is an extremely rare inherited disorder whereby the bones harden, becoming denser, in contrast to more prevalent conditions like osteoporosis, in which the bones become less dense and more brittle, or osteomalacia, in which the bones soften. Osteopetrosis can cause bones to dissolve and break.

This is an AE which is the most common, chronic rheumatic disease of childhood, affecting approximately one per 1,000 children.
This is an AE which is a fairly common form of generalized epilepsy of presumed genetic origin (previously known an idiopathic generalized epilepsy), representing 5-10% of all epilepsy cases.

This is an AE which is an injury to the cushioning and connective tissue between vertebrae, usually caused by excessive strain or trauma to the spine.

This is an AE which is a rare disorder which is easily missed and  presents with non-specific symptoms such as irritability, abdominal pain, decreased appetite and limping.
This is an AE which is a very rare neurologic disorder classically characterised by pronounced startle responses to tactile or acoustic stimuli and hypertonia.
This is an AE which is a rare, sometimes fatal neurological condition linked to the ingestion of the dietary supplement L-tryptophan.

This is an AE which refers to a group of functional disorders leading to abdominal pain due to dysfunction of the Sphincter of Oddi: functional biliary sphincter of Oddi and functional pancreatic sphincter of Oddi disorder.
This is an AE which is the most common inflammatory muscle disease in older adults.
This is an AE which is a complication after a viral infection mainly caused by Influenza A and B viruses.
This is an AE which is a relatively common infectious condition characterized by bullae or vesicles on the tympanic membrane (TM), without affecting the contents of the external or middle ear.
This is an AE which is myopathies that result from defects in biochemical metabolism that primarily affect muscle.
This is an AE which symptoms usually appear about two years after adolescent growth spurt and is significantly more common in males (average age of onset, 15- to 25-year-old).
This is an AE which is a type of chronic inflammation of the muscles (inflammatory myopathy) related to dermatomyositis and inclusion body myositis.

This is an AE which is a form of dilated cardiomyopathy that is defined as a deterioration in cardiac function presenting typically between the last month of pregnancy and up to six months postpartum.
This is an AE which is a birth defect where diaphragmatic  tissue is wholly or largely absent.
This is an AE which is a disorder of a sheet of internal skeletal muscle in humans and other mammals that extends across the bottom of the thoracic cavity .
This is an AE which is an intense itching sensation of the arm usually between the wrist and elbow of either or both arms.
